last_episode_to_air.name: Redwood Renaissance
last_episode_to_air.overview: Inspired by the work of Leonardo da Vinci, the crew builds a gigantic medieval workshop for the biggest amusement trade show in the world, making this their most ambitious build ever.

name: Redwood Kings
overview: Fraternal twins Ron and John Daniels run their tree house and theming business, Daniel's Wood Land.

episodes.name: Pilot
episodes.overview: In the heart of California's cowboy country, twin brothers build incredible creations from majestic hunks of reclaimed redwood, including an elaborate, Hobbit-themed playhouse for the pre-teen daughters of a wealthy repeat customers from the Bay Area.

episodes.name: Shiver Me Timbers
episodes.overview: The Daniels are commissioned by a San Diego couple to build an pirate-themed treehouse for their grandchildren. Back home in Paso Robles, a popular local brewery hires the duo to create a drinking table from the cross-section of a 1,500-year-old Sequoia.

episodes.name: South Dakota Shoot Out
episodes.overview: A returning client hires Ron and John to construct a 10-gun, camping-themed shooting gallery featuring dozens of dancing ducks, goofy prairie dogs and the star of the show, a heckling animatronic hillbilly bear, for his flagship store.

episodes.name: Gold Rush Roadhouse
episodes.overview: When a farmer from central California wants to create the ultimate roadside attraction for travelers, he recruits Daniels Wood Land for the project. With a tight deadline, the guys design an authentic millhouse that pays tribute to the gold rush days.

episodes.name: San Francisco Dungeon
episodes.overview: The Daniels Wood Land team is commissioned to create a dungeon attraction in San Francisco's historic Fisherman's Wharf. The guys then rush off to Huntsville, AL, where they install a 3,000-year-old timeline log at a wild animal park.

episodes.name: Playhouse of Dreams
episodes.overview: In the heart of California's cowboy country, twin brothers build incredible creations from majestic hunks of reclaimed redwood, including an elaborate playhouse for the daughters of wealthy customers from the Bay Area. Includes new facts.

episodes.name: Ships Ahoy
episodes.overview: When the team receives a call from The Marine Museum of the Great Lakes in Ontario, Canada. The museum wants three large-scale replicas of ships that sank in the Great Lakes during the previous three centuries.

episodes.name: Monkey Mansion Dream House
episodes.overview: The team has been hired to build a custom treehouse for a family in Sunnyside, Washington. But with three kids, including one with special needs, and another on the way, their design must be extraordinary and touch on a range of ages and personalities.

episodes.name: Holly Madison's Chicks
episodes.overview: In the Season 2 premiere, model Holly Madison wants a chicken coop for her husband's feathered friends. Also: John carves a pair of foxes.

episodes.name: Hog Wild in the Heartland
episodes.overview: A cartoon-theme clubhouse is built on a pig farm in Indiana during a burst of cold weather.

episodes.name: Coney Island Shoot Out
episodes.overview: A shooting gallery with a Coney Island theme uses infrared beams and electronics to evoke the carnival games of yesteryear.

episodes.name: Redwood Renaissance
episodes.overview: Inspired by the work of Leonardo da Vinci, the crew builds a gigantic medieval workshop for the biggest amusement trade show in the world, making this their most ambitious build ever.
